At least 16 people have received medical care following a taxi accident on Grayston Bridge in Sandton. JOHANNESBURG - At least 16 people were injured in a taxi accident on Grayston Bridge in Sandton on Wednesday. It is understood that the taxi driver lost control of his vehicle and collided with at least three other cars. ER24's Russel Meiring says: The patients were treated and taken to nearby hospitals for further care. The details surrounding this incident are not known, but local authorities are investigating. (Edited by Shimoney Regter)